Reasoning: The paper discusses problems in computer vision and robotics that require representation and estimation of poses on the SE(3) manifold, which are common topics in the cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-categories. The paper also introduces a C++ library for manifold geometry with automatic differentiation and coordinate frame semantics checking, which could be of interest to researchers in the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-categories. Finally, the paper presents experimental results comparing the library to existing open source packages, which could be relevant to researchers in the cs.MS (Mathematical Software) sub-category.
